From: Damien Mascord <tusker@tusker.org>
Subject: [PATCH] net: dsa: mv88e6xxx: return no PCS for internal PHY ports without pcs_ops

Linux 6.12.87 tightened phylink PCS validation. For mv88e6xxx variants
that have internal PHY ports but do not provide pcs_ops,
mv88e6xxx_mac_select_pcs() returning ERR_PTR(-EOPNOTSUPP) causes
phylink_validate_mac_and_pcs() to reject those ports.

Return NULL for internal PHY ports on chips without pcs_ops so phylink
treats them as having no PCS and falls back to MAC capability
validation.

The WatchGuard Firebox T30's 88E6171 uses mv88e6085_ops, which does not
set pcs_ops, so its CPU port also takes this NULL-return path. This is
the actual fix for the T30; there is no companion pcs_validate patch for
mv88e6085.

Signed-off-by: Damien Mascord <tusker@tusker.org>

---
--- a/drivers/net/dsa/mv88e6xxx/chip.c
+++ b/drivers/net/dsa/mv88e6xxx/chip.c
@@ -868,13 +868,25 @@ mv88e6xxx_mac_select_pcs(struct phylink_
 {
 	struct dsa_port *dp = dsa_phylink_to_port(config);
 	struct mv88e6xxx_chip *chip = dp->ds->priv;
-	struct phylink_pcs *pcs = ERR_PTR(-EOPNOTSUPP);
+	/*
+	 * Ports with internal PHYs have no PCS. Return NULL so phylink
+	 * treats it as "no PCS present" and skips PCS validation,
+	 * falling through to MAC capabilities instead.
+	 * Returning ERR_PTR(-EOPNOTSUPP) causes a validation failure in
+	 * phylink_validate_mac_and_pcs() introduced in kernel 6.12.87.
+	 *
+	 * Note: the WatchGuard Firebox T30 (88E6171, mv88e6085_ops) has
+	 * no pcs_ops set, so its CPU port also reaches this NULL-return
+	 * path. This patch is the fix for that hardware too.
+	 */
+	if (!chip->info->ops->pcs_ops) {
+		if (mv88e6xxx_phy_is_internal(chip, dp->index))
+			return NULL;
+		return ERR_PTR(-EOPNOTSUPP);
+	}
 
-	if (chip->info->ops->pcs_ops)
-		pcs = chip->info->ops->pcs_ops->pcs_select(chip, dp->index,
-							   interface);
-
-	return pcs;
+	return chip->info->ops->pcs_ops->pcs_select(chip, dp->index,
+					    interface);
 }
 
 static int mv88e6xxx_mac_prepare(struct phylink_config *config,
